00:25:43,083 --> 00:25:46,867
I need to break him.
All that goodness shit.

235
00:25:48,872 --> 00:25:52,857
Does it involve the pear pie?
Espen says you talk about a pie.

236
00:25:52,887 --> 00:25:56,389
It's an apple pie, okay?
It doesn't matter.

237
00:25:57,200 --> 00:26:00,967
I said that I would bake a pie
and the idiot won't let up.

238
00:26:01,145 --> 00:26:02,678
He says that the Devil is testing us

239
00:26:04,725 --> 00:26:07,131
because birds are eating the apples.

240
00:26:14,473 --> 00:26:15,677
Do you need help?

241
00:26:15,707 --> 00:26:19,161
Who the fuck do you
think you're talking to?

242
00:26:24,200 --> 00:26:25,400
See you.

243
00:26:49,995 --> 00:26:52,177
Go on.
Get them!

244
00:26:53,872 --> 00:26:55,896
Don't be afraid.
Go on. Get them.

245
00:26:56,854 --> 00:26:58,462
He's making them nervous.

246
00:26:58,698 --> 00:27:03,283
- They don't fucking care about the fucking cat.

247
00:27:03,332 --> 00:27:07,167
- They're looking right at him.
- Yes. Lambert is not working.

248
00:27:07,200 --> 00:27:09,511
My granddad
had a cherry tree.

249
00:27:10,347 --> 00:27:15,212
It was attacked by birds, so he shot
a few in the morning and evening.

250
00:27:16,903 --> 00:27:19,133
Shot them?
With a gun?

251
00:27:20,394 --> 00:27:21,954
No, a waffle iron.

252
00:27:22,692 --> 00:27:25,633
Of course it was a gun.
What gun?

253
00:27:26,778 --> 00:27:27,978
One like this.

254
00:27:31,309 --> 00:27:32,509
You know what?

255
00:27:32,832 --> 00:27:36,344
I think that we should try it.
Can you take them from there?

256
00:27:36,635 --> 00:27:41,927
We can use guns?
For fuck's sake, why didn't you say so?

257
00:27:48,582 --> 00:27:50,142
- Well...
- Lambert?

258
00:27:51,497 --> 00:27:53,057
Lambert, are you okay?

259
00:27:54,911 --> 00:27:56,590
What just happened?

260
00:28:02,621 --> 00:28:03,406
He's dead.

261
00:28:03,661 --> 00:28:07,148
- It was a shitty cat anyhow.
- He shot my cat.

262
00:28:07,442 --> 00:28:10,442
Let's stop with the accusations.
It was an old cat.

263
00:28:10,776 --> 00:28:15,146
He just happened to fall down
while we were shooting.

264
00:28:16,020 --> 00:28:18,420
If you want
to discuss it now we can.

265
00:28:20,200 --> 00:28:21,160
Okay.

266
00:28:24,840 --> 00:28:28,517
We talked about your grandfather.
Do you know what I think?

267
00:28:31,200 --> 00:28:33,600
I think
it's going to be a good day.

268
00:28:44,769 --> 00:28:48,369
It's too bad that Khalid won't come in
when we're making his favorite food.

269
00:28:49,200 --> 00:28:52,124
- He's embarrassed about Lambert.
- Where did he get the gun?

270
00:28:53,230 --> 00:28:57,297
- Is he a terrorist?
- He wants to return to Saudi Arabia.

271
00:28:59,121 --> 00:29:01,860
You should see his dream house.
It's really nice.

272
00:29:01,902 --> 00:29:05,539
With a little more money from
a few more Statoil stations, he can finally go home.

273
00:29:06,035 --> 00:29:11,187
- Why not just rob a bank?
- Khalid is very committed to politics.

274
00:29:11,200 --> 00:29:15,351
He only robs multinational companies.
That's why he robs Statoil stations.

275
00:29:15,691 --> 00:29:22,428
Statoil stole his father's land for the
oil. Khalid is taking back his property.

276
00:29:22,668 --> 00:29:25,943
- Statoil is Norwegian.
- No, I don't think so.

277
00:29:25,997 --> 00:29:31,138
- Statoil is Norwegian!
- Remember to tell Khalid that.

278
00:29:31,200 --> 00:29:35,581
- So Ivan knows what he's doing?
- Yes. Ivan just wants him to be calm.

279
00:29:36,512 --> 00:29:38,312
Ivan is not exactly normal.

280
00:29:40,527 --> 00:29:43,527
The anniversary
of his wife's death is coming up.

281
00:29:44,340 --> 00:29:47,657
- He had a wife?
- Yes, Linda.

282
00:29:48,159 --> 00:29:53,649
She took some pills and killed herself
because they had a handicapped son.

283
00:29:54,676 --> 00:30:00,751
He's got cerebral palsy. He can't
move at all. She couldn't take that.

284
00:30:08,419 --> 00:30:09,619
Can I come in?

285
00:30:10,622 --> 00:30:15,560
Adam, there sure is no shortage of
recipes for apple pie in this world.

286
00:30:27,278 --> 00:30:29,678
It looks like we've
won round one.

287
00:30:37,613 --> 00:30:41,060
What a handsome man. Your father?

288
00:30:41,319 --> 00:30:41,951
That's Hitler.

289
00:30:42,200 --> 00:30:42,779
No.

290
00:30:43,865 --> 00:30:45,302
Hitler had a beard.

291
00:30:47,926 --> 00:30:53,196
Ah, you're right. I'm thinking of that
Russian guy. Very well..

292
00:30:54,387 --> 00:30:58,893
Hitler's enemies didn't
take him seriously either.

293
00:30:59,933 --> 00:31:03,721
Don't you think that I do?
That's just plain rude.

294
00:31:08,122 --> 00:31:11,343
Old Paul Nordkap--in the
hospital with no will to live -

295
00:31:11,690 --> 00:31:14,624
- he was a bigger Nazi than anyone.

296
00:31:15,192 --> 00:31:17,866
Why do you think
they ask me to cheer him up?

297
00:31:19,965 --> 00:31:21,713
Wasn't he in a camp?

298
00:31:22,371 --> 00:31:28,119
Sure. He was working there.
He met Goblins and all those folks.

299
00:31:28,589 --> 00:31:31,158
- Goebbels?
- He was probably there as well.

300
00:31:32,083 --> 00:31:36,541
Come with me to visit. Then we
can see who takes who seriously.

301
00:31:37,527 --> 00:31:38,487
Deal?

302
00:31:54,200 --> 00:31:55,400
BOOK OF JOB

303
00:32:28,730 --> 00:32:31,650
Hello!
I'm glad that you could make it.

304
00:32:32,558 --> 00:32:37,580
He's dying. He won't last through
the night. I broke it to him gently.

305
00:32:38,832 --> 00:32:41,232
Well,
let's give him a good sendoff.

306
00:32:41,559 --> 00:32:43,691
- How's the hand?
- Okay.

307
00:32:45,387 --> 00:32:49,645
What about the honker, Ivan?
It took quite a beating.

308
00:32:51,379 --> 00:32:54,379
You don't have to waste
money on perfume anymore, Ivan.

309
00:32:54,878 --> 00:32:58,742
You won't smell anything again.

310
00:32:59,512 --> 00:33:01,072
Yes.
Come on, Adam.

311
00:33:04,347 --> 00:33:08,383
What's up with you, Poul?
Have you lost your appetite?

312
00:33:09,300 --> 00:33:11,422
 I've brought a guest for you.

313
00:33:11,993 --> 00:33:13,813
- Hello. Adam Pedersen.

314
00:33:15,114 --> 00:33:19,138
- Are you feeling a bit low?
- I'm scared.

315
00:33:19,700 --> 00:33:22,123
Relax.
What have you been up to?

316
00:33:22,918 --> 00:33:28,669
- Have the nurses been nicer to you?
- Don't make them. I don't deserve it.

317
00:33:29,183 --> 00:33:32,783
They have been nagging Poul because
of this past but we put a stop to that.

318
00:33:32,840 --> 00:33:35,240
Didn't we, Poul?

319
00:33:37,236 --> 00:33:39,493
Has Miriam been nicer to you?

320
00:33:39,973 --> 00:33:44,396
Yes, she made me hot chocolate
yesterday and tucked me in.

321
00:33:45,317 --> 00:33:50,224
- They are all so nice to me.
- That's good. Don't be upset.

322
00:33:50,395 --> 00:33:55,841
- I don't deserve it. Let me be.
- Everybody deserves to be tucked in.

323
00:33:57,137 --> 00:33:59,825
- Did she fluff your duvet and pillow?
- Yes.

324
00:34:01,700 --> 00:34:02,900
There, there.

325
00:34:03,700 --> 00:34:08,022
I apologize for
trying to skip your sermons.

326
00:34:08,894 --> 00:34:12,576
I just don't like
being inside the church.

327
00:34:12,628 --> 00:34:15,153
- That's all forgotten now.
- I know that's what you always say.

328
00:34:15,184 --> 00:34:23,216
I'm scared, Ivan.
I dare not sleep. I'm so afraid.

329
00:34:23,356 --> 00:34:26,149
Bah!
You have nothing to worry about.

330
00:34:28,012 --> 00:34:33,633
Let's focus on the people who care
for you and all your lovely memories.

331
00:34:33,880 --> 00:34:34,840
Oh God!

332
00:34:38,083 --> 00:34:43,105
Poul, don't cry anymore.
Don't be so hard on yourself.

333
00:34:44,098 --> 00:34:46,581
All has been forgiven.

334
00:34:47,778 --> 00:34:51,830
If you only knew what we did...
All those poor people.

335
00:34:52,700 --> 00:34:57,634
- It can't be forgiven.
- Stop it. Nobody remembers anymore.

336
00:34:59,004 --> 00:35:00,354
Oh God!

337
00:35:00,840 --> 00:35:04,667
Stop your whining.
It's not all that bad!

338
00:35:04,700 --> 00:35:07,700
We all make mistakes
but we don't let them bring us down.

339
00:35:12,207 --> 00:35:14,664
You're...crazy...

340
00:35:16,700 --> 00:35:21,757
Why do you say that? Why spoil
the mood by being rude?

341
00:35:21,809 --> 00:35:26,585
I'd be happy to discuss it,
but this is not the place.

342
00:35:26,632 --> 00:35:29,687
Let's focus on the word of God.

343
00:35:29,700 --> 00:35:33,885
God forgives all, Poul.
God forgives all.

344
00:35:48,169 --> 00:35:49,729
It's always difficult.

345
00:35:51,121 --> 00:35:54,969
Even though I've seen it before
it's still difficult every time.

346
00:36:04,777 --> 00:36:08,170
- Did you discuss your wife's death?
- Yes, I talked to a lot of people.

347
00:36:10,121 --> 00:36:15,041
- A wife's suicide must be painful.
- Yes, it can't be nice.

348
00:36:17,080 --> 00:36:20,345
- Linda didn't take her own life.
- But she took pills?

349
00:36:20,496 --> 00:36:23,468
Yes, but it was an accident.

350
00:36:25,739 --> 00:36:26,939
Accident how?

351
00:36:28,004 --> 00:36:33,135
Christoffer had been playing with her
pills and had put them in a candy dish.

352
00:36:33,708 --> 00:36:38,994
Linda always had a sweet tooth and
she thought they were yellow M&Ms.

353
00:36:40,340 --> 00:36:41,900
Your son Christoffer?

354
00:36:44,379 --> 00:36:48,462
- So he's actually able to move?
- Why wouldn't he be?

355
00:36:49,714 --> 00:36:53,003
- I thought he was paralyzed.
- No, I wish.

356
00:36:53,309 --> 00:36:57,276
There's no slowing him down. Just
yesterday he was playing rounders.

357
00:37:00,371 --> 00:37:02,171
I don't believe you, Ivan.

358
00:37:13,153 --> 00:37:17,410
- I just don't.
- I've never heard anything that crazy.

359
00:37:18,356 --> 00:37:22,721
Has Gunnar tbeen telling tall stories and
playing fast and loose with the truth?

360
00:37:24,229 --> 00:37:26,846
If he has
that's just plain rude.

361
00:37:30,411 --> 00:37:33,105
Why don't you bring your son tomorrow?

362
00:37:33,159 --> 00:37:37,104
He's already coming. He's been
pestering me all week to come.

363
00:37:37,700 --> 00:37:38,565
Good.

364
00:37:40,121 --> 00:37:42,221
Then you can see for yourself.

365
00:38:01,254 --> 00:38:03,054
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

366
00:38:10,098 --> 00:38:12,798
Christoffer, this is Adam.
Adam, Christoffer.

367
00:38:14,700 --> 00:38:18,056
Maybe you could go say hello.
Yum, eggs.

368
00:38:24,301 --> 00:38:26,244
Small mouthfuls.

369
00:38:43,700 --> 00:38:44,722
He's paralyzed.

370
00:38:48,035 --> 00:38:48,855
What did you say?

371
00:38:49,915 --> 00:38:52,670
- I have to go in tower.
- You two stay here.

372
00:38:53,004 --> 00:38:54,915
- I need to shoot more crows.
- Sit down.

373
00:38:59,059 --> 00:38:59,993
He's paralyzed.

374
00:39:02,269 --> 00:39:05,863
Christoffer,
go into daddy's office. Now!

375
00:39:13,317 --> 00:39:16,518
This will not be pleasant to watch.
What did you say?

376
00:39:18,387 --> 00:39:21,026
He's paralyzed.
Isn't he paralyzed, Ivan?

377
00:39:21,425 --> 00:39:22,985
Is he really, Adam?

378
00:39:24,309 --> 00:39:27,220
Yes, he has cerebral palsy.

379
00:39:29,481 --> 00:39:32,877
That is just crazy.
Khalid, what do you have to say?

380
00:39:38,520 --> 00:39:39,034
Khalid?

381
00:39:39,911 --> 00:39:41,111
He does.

382
00:39:42,411 --> 00:39:44,483
Ivan, he's paralyzed.

383
00:39:49,324 --> 00:39:52,194
Your son's a retard.
Your wife killed herself.

384
00:39:52,700 --> 00:39:56,235
Your mother died giving birth to you.
Your dad raped you.

385
00:40:00,184 --> 00:40:03,485
Look at me, Ivan.
Look at me.

386
00:40:07,700 --> 00:40:13,953
You're bleeding from the ear. You're
bleeding from the ear, for fuck's sake!

387
00:40:13,973 --> 00:40:15,173
The other one!

388
00:40:26,700 --> 00:40:29,700
- Ivan was bleeding from an ear.
- That happened to me once.

389
00:40:31,700 --> 00:40:34,684
Just drink milk.
Plenty of milk.

390
00:41:23,871 --> 00:41:25,431
Just give up, Ivan.

391
00:41:31,501 --> 00:41:32,384
Adam.

392
00:41:40,481 --> 00:41:42,003
There's something
you should know.

393
00:41:45,464 --> 00:41:51,334
Christoffer is recovering from
a very nasty bout of the flu.

394
00:41:51,371 --> 00:41:54,248
I'm the first to admit that
he's been a bit sluggish lately.

395
00:41:55,700 --> 00:41:59,685
- Shut the fuck up!
- If one hurts you, turn the other cheek.

396
00:42:01,168 --> 00:42:02,728
God is on my side.

397
00:42:45,622 --> 00:42:48,461
What is his problem?
He needs to be locked up!

398
00:42:50,004 --> 00:42:53,055
I'm not one to gossip -

399
00:42:54,044 --> 00:42:56,867
- but he's always been
considered a phenomenon.

400
00:42:56,898 --> 00:43:00,453
- I don't know if you don't.
- How the hell should I know?

401
00:43:01,700 --> 00:43:06,061
- He's sick. Very sick.
- I bloody well know that.

402
00:43:07,793 --> 00:43:10,795
No, not like that.
Well, he is that, too -

403
00:43:11,811 --> 00:43:12,694
but...

404
00:43:12,858 --> 00:43:16,398
he's terminally ill.

405
00:43:16,793 --> 00:43:19,086
- What's wrong with him?
- Cancer.

406
00:43:21,606 --> 00:43:25,125
He has a brain tumor
the size of a volleyball.

407
00:43:25,278 --> 00:43:30,125
I've never seen anyone
with such a large brain tumor.

408
00:43:30,965 --> 00:43:33,688
I'll bash your face in
if you call him a walking miracle.

409
00:43:33,973 --> 00:43:36,592
Have you heard about
the Ravashi syndrome?

410
00:43:37,270 --> 00:43:40,412
Ravashi was
an Indian footballer -

411
00:43:40,436 --> 00:43:44,555
- who lost both his feet
in a go-kart accident in 1957.

412
00:43:45,245 --> 00:43:52,344
In a state of shock over the accident
he ran home on the stumps of his legs.

413
00:43:52,371 --> 00:43:56,828
His brain blocked the fact
that he had no feet.

414
00:43:57,144 --> 00:43:59,948
For two months
he came to practice.

415
00:44:00,512 --> 00:44:05,229
- He kept his midfield position.
- Without feet?

416
00:44:05,582 --> 00:44:10,749
They were a bad team.
They were maybe in the fifth league.

417
00:44:11,700 --> 00:44:14,464
Ivan has experienced
so much hardship -

418
00:44:14,480 --> 00:44:19,136
- that he needs to find an
explanation in order to live with it.

419
00:44:19,778 --> 00:44:26,079
That's why he thinks that
the Devil has it in for him.

420
00:44:26,700 --> 00:44:31,071
Ivan would say that
everything is a test.

421
00:44:31,700 --> 00:44:36,625
You're a test, his cancer is a test,
his son's handicap is a test.

422
00:44:36,700 --> 00:44:42,777
In Ivan's mind he's locked in
fierce battle with the Devil himself.

423
00:44:43,269 --> 00:44:48,050
Ivan has no mind to lose and he
blocks out everything like Ravashi.

424
00:44:48,700 --> 00:44:55,182
He's in denial about all the bad stuff.
Death, mutilation, hardship, evil.

425
00:44:55,207 --> 00:44:57,940
That simply
doesn't exist in Ivan's world.

426
00:45:01,941 --> 00:45:03,741
Why does he bleed from his ears?

427
00:45:04,176 --> 00:45:10,633
We have asked ourselves that. I think
it's when something comes too close.

428
00:45:11,754 --> 00:45:17,015
Someone once got through to him.
He bled from his ears once before.

429
00:45:17,700 --> 00:45:19,500
That was three years ago.

430
00:45:20,926 --> 00:45:25,426
- What happened?
- You don't know his sister Katinka.

431
00:45:25,480 --> 00:45:29,965
An utter whore.
She fucked everybody.

432
00:45:30,700 --> 00:45:34,901
I even fucked her when she was
here to have her tonsils removed.

433
00:45:35,700 --> 00:45:37,667
When she died
Ivan almost fell to pieces.

434
00:45:38,012 --> 00:45:42,104
He bled from his ears
and got sick.

435
00:45:44,910 --> 00:45:47,997
- What happened then?
- You know Ivan.

436
00:45:48,505 --> 00:45:51,395
A few days later
he was jolly as ever.

437
00:45:53,355 --> 00:45:56,313
You could simply kill him by
making him understand the truth?

438
00:45:57,036 --> 00:45:59,368
Yes, in theory.

439
00:46:18,465 --> 00:46:19,665
Give up, Adam.

440
00:46:21,394 --> 00:46:24,302
God is on my side.
Never forget that.

441
00:46:32,230 --> 00:46:34,030
Hi.
The stove is broken.

442
00:46:34,870 --> 00:46:38,959
- I wanted to make Christoffer a pizza.
- Let's fix it.

443
00:46:38,997 --> 00:46:42,901
- I don't know how.
- We'll get by.

444
00:46:43,113 --> 00:46:46,113
- Where did Christoffer go?
- He's in your office with a woman.

445
00:46:47,121 --> 00:46:53,737
She's quite upset. Her name is Sarah
and she's a real hottie.

446
00:46:54,973 --> 00:47:00,439
When she saw Christoffer she started
screaming. She didn't want coffee.

447
00:47:00,488 --> 00:47:03,712
Well, we'd better...

448
00:47:09,145 --> 00:47:10,945
So nice of you to visit again.

449
00:47:12,333 --> 00:47:15,596
- Has he been good?
- Tell me he isn't yours.

450
00:47:15,770 --> 00:47:20,844
I can't because this is Christoffer.
Have you two been introduced?

451
00:47:20,948 --> 00:47:24,653
How can you say the things you did?

452
00:47:26,669 --> 00:47:27,434
What kind of things?

453
00:47:27,455 --> 00:47:33,031
You said that nothing was wrong
with him. That he could do math.

454
00:47:33,403 --> 00:47:36,961
Yes, he can.
Even the complicated kind.

455
00:47:43,504 --> 00:47:47,889
Adam, maybe you should go get
some of the cookies that Sarah likes.

456
00:48:11,074 --> 00:48:12,788
I'll come too.

457
00:48:18,075 --> 00:48:19,635
Is anyone hungry?

458
00:48:39,402 --> 00:48:43,705
You can hook up the new stove now.
We'll see if this one lasts a bit longer than the last.

459
00:48:44,338 --> 00:48:46,738
- What are you doing?
- Playing a drinking game with coins.

460
00:48:46,848 --> 00:48:51,786
- Gunnar is good.
- But you're pregnant.

461
00:48:51,832 --> 00:48:56,153
- It's a bit late for that.
- We're rewriting an article.

462
00:48:56,231 --> 00:48:59,213
- About what?
- The tigers in the Orient.

463
00:48:59,380 --> 00:49:05,025
Here it says that
there's only 400 left.

464
00:49:05,340 --> 00:49:08,564
It won't be long before they're extinct.

465
00:49:08,957 --> 00:49:12,215
- Like the last round at the pub.
- What do you do then, Gunnar?

466
00:49:12,511 --> 00:49:16,641
- You buy a pint and a chaser.
